## Kubernetes - Resource Limits

apiversion: v1
Kind : pod
metadata : 
   name : pathnex-limit-pod
spec:
  containers:
     - name: app
      image: nginx
      resources:
         limits:
            memory: "250Mi"
            cpu: "500m"

This is a Kubernetes Pod YAML.

The purpose of this YAML is to:

Create a Pod.
Run an Nginx container inside the Pod.
Limit how much CPU and Memory the container can use.

This is commonly used in production so that one application cannot consume all the resources of a Kubernetes node.



## Jenkins Pipeline - Use Environment Variables
You will learn how to **use environment variables in Jenkins pipelines**.

pipeline {
    agent any
    environment {
        INSTITUTE_NAME = "Pathnex"
    }
    stages {
        stage('Print') {
            steps {
                sh 'echo "Welcome to $INSTITUTE_NAME DevOps Training"'
            }
        }
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean package -Dinstitute.name=$INSTITUTE_NAME'
            }
        }
    }
}

## jankins Pipeline - use enviroment variables
you will learn how to **use enviroment variable in jenkins pipelines*

Pipeline {
    agent any
    enviroment {
        Institute_Name = "Pathnex"
    }
    stages {
        stage('print') {
            steps{
                sh 'echo "welcome to $Institute_Name Devops Training"'
            }
